            <V n="text" t="single">
              <T n="single">0x2CDDCD9A<!--String: "A Getaway can be as simple as enjoying a change of pace and staying away from home. The first thing to do will be to get your bearings—take a look at your surroundings and take a look at your Getaway's Schedule. For as long as your Getaway lasts, this will be your home! So explore, get comfortable, claim a bed, and start making friends!\n\nA Getaway has a Schedule, which is an itinerary filled with Activities—these Activities are things that Sims will care about doing, along with their other priorities and wants. The Schedule gives you control of the full Getaway experience. Changing Activities will change what you see happening at the Getaway, and changing Roles will change what kinds of Sims show up, how they behave, and what outfits they wear. As the Getaway unfolds, you can sit back and enjoy the show—or be the leader of the experience and stir things up however you like.\n\nAs Sims do different kinds of Activities in a Getaway, they will change, and they might develop new traits, special bonds, or earn unique rewards. Many kinds of adventure and rewards await your Sims—whether it's an exploring the outdoors, competing with other talented Sims, or just kicking their feet up, there's no wrong way to get away.\n\nIf you'd like to learn even more about all the cool things you do with Getaway Schedules and Roles, or perhaps learn about Getaway Rules and how they can transform your Getaway, check out these Lessons below!"--></T>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="enabled">
              <T n="enabled">0x7C0E16FF<!--String: "Introduction to Getaways"--></T>
            </V>
            <L n="ui_responses">
